Brendan Rodgers insisted that Dejan Lovren was happy to take a penalty before his miss ended Liverpool's Europa League hopes in Istanbul on Thursday.

Liverpool, who famously won the Champions League in a shootout at the Ataturk Stadium in 2005, suffered their first ever European defeat on penalties at the fourth attempt.

Lovren, who has struggled to live up to his £20million transfer fee from Southampton last summer, took his spot-kick ahead of more attacking players like Raheem Sterling with the teams tied at 4-4 in the shootout, and fired over the bar.

